This paper deals with the problem of single image super-resolution using a novel approach that incorporates categorical information to improve the quality of the output image. This involves multitask learning, where the decoder architecture is able to extract and use semantic information for both image super-resolution and semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these areas are also relevant to the paper's focus on deep neural networks and image processing.
